  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka President\u2019s policy direction correct, but could be a cuckoo egg: Harsha",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka President Ranil Wickremesinghe\u2019s policy direction in the budget is correct but whether it can be implemented while working with a party with opposite ideas, Samagi Jana Balawegaya legislator Harsha de Silva said.",
        "\u201cThis is the direction of the economic policy of the President,\u201d de Silva said. \u201cWe are not against this plan.",
        "\u201cThis is what Bangladesh is doing. This is what Vietnam is doing.\u201d",
        "The SLPP had consistently opposed all measures aimed to develop the country.",
        "However, analysts say both countries had long periods of monetary stability. Bangladesh for about 10 years, and Vietnam for longer periods.",
        "\u201cRanil Wickremesinghe had tried to do it before,\u201d de Silva said. \u201cBut the SLPP and Rajapaksa ideology opposed them for political gain. We saw it happen with the Sri Lanka-Singapore free trade agreement.\u201d",
        "\u201cWill these people agree to this? Will a person in the custody of the SLPP be allowed to do it? We do not think.",
        "\u201cRanil Wickremesinghe\u2019s economic strategy is like a keol egg in a crow\u2019s nest.\u201d",
        "The Samagi Jana Balawegaya believes in individual freedom, economic freedom and social justice, he said.",
        "De Silva said he was opposed to the arrest of protestors under the Wickremesinghe administration. (Colombo/Sep31/2022)"
      ],
